snippet.textDisplay:
Not many people will see this comment since this video is 2 years old, but I was feeling down and came here to listen to this masterpiece and I understood something. 

The line "saari khushian mil jawan te piche ki reh jana" is actually so deep that understanding it can release one of all the tensions in the world. The fact that if you get something you desire, you do not care for it as much. Not being able to achieve it makes us struggle, and that struggle reminds us that we are human. It is our humanity that connects us to reality. If we get everything we wish for, we lose our purpose. 

It's such a beautiful message put into such a beautiful line.
